EVALUATION MANUAL
=================

Installation
------------

1) Move to the eprover/ directory of the submitted archive.
2) Run ./local_build

As a result two binaries will be created in eprover/bin directory:
  1) eprover-fo : this binary runs E 2.3 in FOL mode
  2) eprover-ho : this binary runs E 2.3 in LFHOL mode


Problems
--------

Directory ehoh_problems/ contains the problems used in our experimentation.
In the following we describe the structure of its subdirectories that
contain different categories of the problems we evaluated our
artifact on:

ehoh_problems/			
├── applicative				# applicatively encoded problems
│   ├── app_sh_32_fo		# FOL Sledgehammer problems using 32 facts
│   ├── app_sh_32_ho		# LFHOL Sledgehammer problems using 32 facts
│   ├── app_sh_512_fo		# FOL Sledgehammer problems using 512 facts
│   ├── app_sh_512_ho		# LFHOL Sledgehammer problems using 512 facts
│   ├── app_tptp_fo			# TPTP FOL problems
│   └── app_tptp_ho			# TPTP LFHOL problems
└── original				# original, unprocessed problems
    ├── sh_32_fo 			# FOL Sledgehammer problems using 32 facts
    ├── sh_32_ho 			# LFHOL Sledgehammer problems using 32 facts	
    ├── sh_512_fo 			# FOL Sledgehammer problems using 512 facts	
    ├── sh_512_ho 			# LFHOL Sledgehammer problems using 512 facts	
    ├── tptp_fo 			# TPTP FOL problems
    └── tptp_ho 			# TPTP LFHOL problems 
        

Configurations
--------------

The bin/ folder contains 7 different configurations which we used
to evaluate E 2.3:

1) a_ho: Auto mode, LFHOL version
2) a_fo: Auto mode, FOL version
3) as_ho: Auto-schedule mode, LFHOL version
4) as_fo: Auto-schedule mode, FOL version
5) b_ho: Best-of-manual, LFHOL version
6) b_fo: Best-of-manual, FOL version
7) hb_ho: Higher-order best-of-manual, LFHOL version


Running the experiments
-----------------------

To run the experiments automatically we have prepared the script
run_configuration.py that runs selected configuration on
all files in the selected folder. More precisely

  "python3 run_configuration.py <configuration_file CF> <root_folder RF> <timeout T> <results_file RES_F>"

will run E using configuration CF on all files in directory hierarchy rooted
at RF with the CPU limit T. The results will be saved in the file RES_F.
Results will contain the path to the problem, answer (status) of the prover
and  time the prover took to finish. When the script finishes, a small summary
will be printed containing the number of problems on which each prover
reported a certain status.

An example run is:

  "python3 run_configuration.py ./a_ho ./ehoh_problems/original/sh_32_ho 60 sh_32_fo_res.csv"

which will run E 2.3 compiled in higher-order mode, using auto mode on original
LFHOL Sledgehammer problems generated using 32 Isabelle facts. This result obtained using
this example corresponds to the intersection of seventh row and fifth column of Table 1
of our paper.